2011-01-24 21:18  alpha@paranoici.org
	* trunk/ardesia/win32/build_installer: 
        - The script now auto builds the ardesia iscc file 
          Now is not required anymore to open and
	  run the ardesia iscc file You also need InnoSetup
	  (http://www.innosetup.org) with iscc in your PATH In order to
	  add iscc in the PATH msys enviroment you must add something like
	  this in the .profile file located in your home directory: export
	  IS_DIR=$PROGRAMFILES/Inno\ Setup\ 5 export PATH=$IS_DIR:$PATH
	  where IS_DIR is the Inno Setup installation folder


2011-01-24 20:15  alpha@paranoici.org
	* trunk/ardesia/win32/build_installer:
        - Fix the script to prepare the folder used by the Inno Setup script 
          "ardesia.iss".
          In order to create the package you must: 
          - Build and Install mingw, the needed libraries and ardesia following 
            the instruction located on http://code.google.com/p/ardesia/wiki/CompileFromRepoOnWindows
          - Install inno setup from http://www.jrsoftware.org/isdl.php 
          - Run the installer shell script to prepare the folder that will be
	    used by the inno setup installation builder sh win32/build_installer 
          - Open with "Inno Setup" the ardesia.iss and run it


