2011-01-07 15:15  alpha@paranoici.org
	* trunk/ardesia/src/ardesia.c: 
        - Add a warning if the screen doesn't support RGBA channel 
          REGARDS: The RGBA channel is needed to have the transparency 
                   and in order to run Ardesia fine. 
          In Ubuntu 10.10 with xcompmgr the RGBA is not supported, It is
          a problem in the startlxde script see the bug 589763 in launchpad.
          WORKAROUND: open the /usr/bin/startlubuntu and comment the line
                      export XLIB_SKIP_ARGB_VISUALS=1
  

